Technical Vocational Training and Education institutions have been urged to foster collaboration with relevant stakeholders through the Kenya Education for Employment Programme. TVET director Meshack Opwora said the Kitale National Polytechnic has taken up the partnership with colleges and institutions in Canada. More on this : Sh40 million to equip, revive TVET centres The government initiated the project through an agreement under KEFEP focusing on Agriculture and Engineering. Opwora spoke at the Kitale National Polytechnic graduation ceremony on Wednesday. He said through the partnership, several polytechnic staffers have gone for training in Canada. Click here for more political news